White House Chief of Staff Reince Priebus, OMB Director Mick Mulvaney, Attorney General Jeff Sessions, and Secretary of Homeland Security John Kelly all spoke about President Trump's accomplishments in the first 100 days of his presidency. Priebus highlighted achievements such as a decrease in border crossings, withdrawal from the TPP, and the appointment of Neil Gorsuch to the Supreme Court. Mulvaney mentioned that more legislation has been signed into law and executive orders issued than in the past 50 years, with a focus on reducing government regulations. Sessions emphasized the administration's commitment to ending illegal immigration and border security. Kelly discussed the targeting of criminals who are in the country illegally and encouraged reporting of crimes while ensuring anonymity for those reporting.